Introduction¶

Lade has a script and is thinking of the director and main act that would bring her characters to life whilst making a large profit and gaining popularity. She contacts Kareemat(me) who is a Data Analyst in the movie industry on advise. Lade also informs Kareemat that her scripts genre is mostly Drama.

Kareemat carries out an analysis using the Movie Database dataset (tmdb-movies) which has relevant columns that would foster her analysis. The tmdb-movies dataset has several columns and rows featuring:

Columns Description: id, imdb_id : unique id or imdb id for each movie on TMDB popularity: a metric used to measure the popularity of the movie. budget:the total budget of the moviein USD. revenue:the total revenue of the movie in USD. original_title: the original title of the movie. cast:the names of the cast of the movie separated by "|". homepage: the website of the movie (if it existed). director:name(s) of the director(s) of the movie (separated by "|" if there are more than one director). tagline:a catchphrase describing the movie. keywords: keywords related to the movie. overview:summary of the plot of the movie. runtime:total runtime of the movie in minutes. genres: genres of the movie separated by "|". production_companies:production compan(y/ies) of the movie. release_date:release date of the movie. vote_count:number of voters of te movie. vote_average:the average user rating of the movie release_year:release year of the movie (from 1960 to 2015) budget_adj:the total budget of the moviein USD in terms of 2010 dollars, accounting for inflation over time. revenue_adj:the total budget of the movie in USD in terms of 2010 dollars, accounting for inflation over time. 4

Kareemat has to use this columns to advise Lade on:

  1. Directors and Actors that would generate high profit for her scripts
  2. Directors and Actors that would deliver very popular movies

Defining Functions¶

In [109]:
def group_max(df,x,y):
    '''
    This function is to give an output of recipients
    of the max count after being grouped.
    The first line of code creates a dataframe for each group
    with their counts.
    The second line of code gets the index of where 
    the counts column is equal to the max count
    for each group.
    The dataframe corresponding to the rows is returned
    '''
    grp_cnt_df = df.groupby(x)[y].value_counts().rename('counts').reset_index()
    index = grp_cnt_df.groupby([x])['counts'].transform('max') == grp_cnt_df['counts']
    return grp_cnt_df.loc[index][[x,y,'counts']].set_index(x,y)
In [110]:
def piechart(df,x,y,title):
    '''
    This function is to
    plot a piechart
    '''
    data = df[df[x] == y]['main_genre']
    data = data.value_counts()
    labels = data.index
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    data.plot(kind='pie',labels=labels,autopct='%1.2f%%')
    plt.title(title);

Creating New Columns¶

In this dataset, the main columns of focus have multiple infos, Kareemat assumes the first info is the most important,so she picks that out and puts it in new columns for better analysis. Those columns include:

cast - the cast column has multiple people director - a good number of the movies have one directors but some have multiple genres - There are multiple genres as expected but I'm creating a new column for the first genre production_companies - Multiple production companies also

In [119]:
#Assuming the lead act is the first written on the cast
#The first genre is the main genre
#The first production 
df['lead_actor'] = df['cast'].str.split('|',expand=True)[0]
df['main_director'] = df['director'].str.split('|',expand=True)[0]
df['main_genre'] = df['genres'].str.split('|',expand=True)[0]
df['main_production_company'] = df['production_companies'].str.split('|',expand=True)[0]

Findings¶

  1. Steven Spielberg is the most popular director and also the most profitable director
  2. Steven Spielberg's is good in a variety of genres but his main genres are drama and adventure
  3. Tom Cruise is one of the most profitable actors with his main genre being drama
  4. Tom Hanks is also one of the most profitable actors with his main genre being comedy
  5. Drama,Action and Comedy are all very profitable and popular genres
  6. The most popular actors are Johnny Depp and Nicolas Sage
  7. Nicolas Sage is the actor with the most losses
  8. Renny Harlin is the director with the most losses
  9. Universal Pictures production company had the most profit

Limitations¶

  1. Assuming the first values in columns cast,director,genres and production_companies were the most important, therefore this analysis does not cover the successive values in each of these columns
  2. The Dependent variables in this analysis(i.e. popularity ad profit) had a lot of outliers so they were not dropped
  3. Columns revenue_adj and budget_adj had a lot of zero values which had to be dropped
  4. Columns cast,director,genres and production_companies which had null values were filled with unknown
  5. There were a large number of drama, action and comedy genres in the dataset

Kareemat's Advise to Lade¶

It will be safe option for Lade to take her script to Steven Spielberg with her lead actor being Tom Cruise since it is a drama. She can also decide to add little comedy and bring on Tom Hanks as a supporting act. As a plus she should consider using Universal Pictures production company.
